<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf3d96b4f-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc" identifier="/us/usc/t35/s285"><num value="285">§ 285.</num><heading> Attorney fees</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The court in exceptional cases may award reasonable attorney fees to the prevailing party.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf3d96b50-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc">(<ref href="/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950">July 19, 1952, ch. 950</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/66/813">66 Stat. 813</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf3d96b51-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idf3d96b52-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., § 70, part (R.S. 4921, amended (1) <ref href="/us/act/1897-03-03/ch391/s6">Mar. 3, 1897, ch. 391, § 6</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/29/694">29 Stat. 694</ref>, (2) <ref href="/us/act/1922-02-18/ch58/s8">Feb. 18, 1922, ch. 58, § 8</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/42/392">42 Stat. 392</ref>, (3) <ref href="/us/act/1946-08-01/ch726/s1">Aug. 1, 1946, ch. 726, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/60/778">60 Stat. 778</ref>).</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">This section is substantially the same as the corresponding provision in R.S. 4921; “in exceptional cases” has been added as expressing the intention of the present statute as shown by its legislative history and as interpreted by the courts.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
